Pieter-Louis Myburgh, News24What started as a tiny band of protesters outside the Gupta family's estate in Johannesburg on Friday morning has grown into large, lively crowd of picketers.As struggle songs resonated outside the infamous family's upmarket estate in the leafy suburb of Saxonwold, posters demanding the resignation of President Jacob Zuma were the order of the day.Police at the scene cordoned off the road, a police helicopter circled above the estate, and at least 20 police officers and private security guards kept a close watch on the more than 100 people gathered in front of the compound's main entrance.News24 reporter Sharlene Rood is live outside the Gupta compund in Saxonwold.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.